This paper deals with evolutionary algorithms and optimization, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-field of neural networks and learning (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different topologies for migration in island models, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of fitness functions and local optima, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the performance of different migration topologies, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DM).
